<Author>scooper99
<Content>Went for a conference I booked rooms for myself and several others. Check-in was not smooth and the CSR was spastic and needed the manager to walk her through step by step. The meeting space (the ballroom) on the second floor was great. The food was amazing! Everything was cooked properly and was seasoned like I would at home. The waitstaff was kind and performed seemlessly.My stay was almost ruined by housekeeping. I wanted ice. Go get the ice bucket right. Can't there are moldy grapes in the bottom. I call for another bucket. I call again. I call again. Finally someone brings me a new bucket, but they leave the old bucket with the moldy grapes and they don't leave any liners for the new bucket.I finally took the bucket with its content downstairs. I was helped by a friendly lady apologized, she later who sent Fiji water to my room. My problem was I could not even relax wondering what else wasn't cleaned...The hotel wasn't even a month old and I understand some kinks need to be worked out but I wish I wasn't involved. 
