<Author>OzExpat
<Content>Nice addition to downtown Phoenix The new Sheraton in downtown Phoenix is definitely a nice addition. It is a typical large business oriented hotel, but it has a good location and good amenities. We stayed on the Club floor - although the hotel seemed almost empty the night we were there we were put in a room way at the end of the corridor on the side of the hotel with only one small window. Nicely furnished rooms but small and with just the one small window, not able to fully appreciate the great views from the 28th floor. The Club Lounge was very nice - Stacey who works there was great!! She made our stay. Nice enough pool area on the 4th floor, but it's a little bland. Staff were great everywhere - very friendly and attentive. Cafe in the lobby with free internet (if you're a guest) was nice and the lobby bar is a good place to relax. Didn't try the restaurant, although we came back a week later at 9:45pm on a Friday night and were turned away as they were no longer serving food - not even after theater dessert. When will Phoenix start acting like a big city!Overall, decent place to stay as there are not too many options in downtown Phoenix. 
